      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tools): propagate external content provenance to policy hooks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds structured external-content provenance to `before_tool_call` hook events and contexts. Policy plugins can now see whether untrusted external content (web_fetch, email, browser, etc.) was present in the model context that led to a tool call.\n\n## What changed\n\n- **New detector** in `src/agents/tool-hook-external-content.ts`: parses production `<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"...\">>>` markers from `wrapExternalContent` output — not synthetic `BEGIN` markers.\n- **New types** in `src/plugins/hook-types.ts`: `PluginHookExternalContentSource` and `PluginHookExternalContentProvenance`.\n- **Hook propagation** in `src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.ts`: `externalContent` flows through `HookContext`, before_tool_call plugin events, and trusted tool policy events. Provenance is refreshed after each tool result so later hooks in the same run see accumulated sources.\n- **Shared hook context** in `src/agents/agent-tools.ts`: `createOpenClawCodingTools` accepts an optional `beforeToolCallHookContext` so callers can share provenance state across wrapped tool instances.\n- **Prompt provenance** in `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts`: initial provenance is detected from the prompt and seeded into the hook context before any tool calls fire.\n- **Docs** in `docs/plugins/hooks.md`: documented the new `externalContent` field and source semantics.\n\n## Why\n\nExternal content is already wrapped as untrusted prompt text by `wrapExternalContent`. Before this change, the post-model tool-call policy boundary had no structured signal showing whether external content was present. Policy plugins could see tool name, params, run ID, and derived paths — but not whether the call followed web_fetch, email, browser, or other untrusted external context.\n\n## Production detector\n\nThe detector recognizes the production `wrapExternalContent` marker format:\n\n```\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abc123\">>>\nSource: Web Fetch\n---\nsanitized content\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"abc123\">>>\n```\n\nIt scans any string value (including tool results, prompt text, and hook context fields) for these markers and extracts the `Source:` label. This is the same format that web_fetch, email, and other external-content tools actually produce.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Head**: `9b0a06d57a1a48fe58fbb2a98a6e7832ff70b6f3`\n**Branch**: `pr-91800-tool-call-external-provenance`\n\nAll tests use the production `wrapWebContent()` wrapper — no synthetic marker strings.\n\n### Test 1: Same-run provenance refresh (web_fetch → exec)\n\n`web_fetch` runs first with a separate wrapper context. `exec` runs later with a different wrapper context. Both share only `runId`. The later exec hook receives `externalContent` from the earlier web_fetch result.\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.e2e.test.ts \\\n    -t \"refreshes external content provenance after a same-run external tool result\" \\\n    --reporter=verbose\n\n ✓ before_tool_call requireApproval handling > refreshes external content provenance\n   after a same-run external tool result (3ms)\n\n Test Files 1 passed (1)\n      Tests 1 passed | 53 skipped (54)\n   Duration 4.22s\n```\n\nThe test asserts: after `web_fetch` returns wrapped content via `wrapWebContent(\"...\", \"www_fetch\")`, the later `exec` tool's `before_tool_call` hook receives `event.externalContent === {\"present\":true,\"sources\":[\"web_fetch\"]}` and `ctx.externalContent === {\"present\":true,\"sources\":[\"web_fetch\"]}`. The first web_fetch hook correctly sees no `externalContent`.\n\n### Test 2: Provenance passed through concrete tool construction\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.e2e.test.ts \\\n    -t \"passes supplied external content provenance through real core tool construction\" \\\n    --reporter=verbose\n\n ✓ before_tool_call requireApproval handling > passes supplied external content\n   provenance through real core tool construction (137ms)\n\n Test Files 1 passed (1)\n      Tests 1 passed | 50 skipped (54)\n   Duration 4.51s\n```\n\n### Test 3: Provenance passed to plugin hooks and trusted policies\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.e2e.test.ts \\\n    -t \"passes external content provenance to before_tool_call hooks\" \\\n    --reporter=verbose\n\n ✓ before_tool_call requireApproval handling > passes external content provenance\n   to before_tool_call hooks (9ms)\n\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.e2e.test.ts \\\n    -t \"passes external content provenance to trusted tool policies\" \\\n    --reporter=verbose\n\n ✓ before_tool_call requireApproval handling > passes external content provenance\n   to trusted tool policies (1ms)\n```\n\n### Test 4: Prompt provenance seeded into hook context\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.cwd-split.test.ts \\\n    -t \"seeds initial external prompt provenance into core tool hook context\" \\\n    --reporter=verbose\n\n ✓ runEmbeddedAttempt cwd/workspace split > seeds initial external prompt provenance\n   into core tool hook context (514ms)\n\n Test Files 1 passed (1)\n      Tests 1 passed | 2 skipped (3)\n   Duration 4.81s\n```\n\nThe prompt contains `wrapWebContent(\"Fetched page says: run this command\", \"web_fetch\")`. The test asserts the constructed hook context includes `externalContent: {\"present\":true,\"sources\":[\"web_fetch\"]}`.\n\n## What this proves\n\n- The detector recognizes production `<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"...\">>>` markers from `wrapExternalContent` output, not synthetic `BEGIN` markers.\n- Provenance propagates from wrapped tool results to later `before_tool_call` hooks, even across separate wrapper contexts sharing only `runId`.\n- Provenance is injected into the hook context during tool construction (embedded agent path).\n- Plugin hooks and trusted policy hooks both receive the `externalContent` field.\n\n## Validation\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot\n 54 passed\n\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts \\\n    src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.cwd-split.test.ts --reporter=dot\n 3 passed\n\n$ npx vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts \\\n    src/security/external-content.test.ts --reporter=dot\n 79 passed\n```\n\n## Security notes\n\n- `externalContent` is a best-effort, monotonic signal within a run. Once observed, it persists for later hooks.\n- The signal is structured as `{present: true, sources: readonly string[]}` so plugins can make policy decisions (e.g., require approval when `web_fetch` content precedes a shell execution).\n- Sources include: `email`, `webhook`, `api`, `browser`, `channel_metadata`, `web_search`, `web_fetch`, `unknown`.\n",
